nt-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.25pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">I am replying in a personal capacity rather than on behalf of the Energy and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.1pt">Climate Change Committee. I draw in particular on my experience as Chair of the Environmental Audit Committee in the last Parliament. I was conscious of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.15pt">the difficulty of maintaining the focus of the Committee as the date for a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.25pt">possible General Election drew nearer.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.4pt">Against this background I believe that fixed-term Parliaments and the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.25pt">consequent greater certainty about the dates of General Elections will be helpful </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">to the work of Select Committees.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.4pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">In the current Parliament it will be easier for the Energy and Climate Change </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Committee to plan its work </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> right through until the spring of 2015 in the clear knowledge that the House of Commons will still be in session at that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.15pt">time. This will mean that both Members and Committee staff can remain </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.3pt">focused on completing a fuller </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.3pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.3pt"> than would be possible if there was </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">uncertainty about the date of the General Election.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">Inevitably the ability to achieve consensus in Committee reports may be eroded </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">as election campaigning begins in earnest but even this consideration will be </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.05pt">made somewhat easier by the removal of uncertainty about the election date. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:0.55pt">As Members and Committee staff become accustomed to fixed term </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.1pt">Parliaments, there may be greater scope for better strategic planning, right at the start of a Parliament, on what the Committee wants to achieve over five </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.35pt">years. This may, for example, help Committees to take a proactive approach to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">scrutiny and help set the agenda in its policy area.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 3.6pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.2pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 375.15pt 0pt 0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">9 January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>